node.text:
Beware! 🚫 There is a new editing app out there that can do crazy things such as make you taller, paste on fake 6 pack abs, and even make your neck more elongated-all from your cell phone.

It’s wild to me that there are more and more of these editing apps coming out that prey on our deep insecurities and perceived flaws.

I wanted to share this with you ladies gents so that you will slowly stop comparing yourselves to strangers on the internet. That girl you see probably doesn’t even look like herself in real life. So, the next time you look in the mirror please remind yourself of this! You are worthy

Maybe she’s born worn it. Maybe it’s an editing app!

node.title: My Breast Implants Are Poisoning Me!

node.text:
SIDE BOOTY WORKOUT-no gym or equipment needed!

Anyone who's trained with me knows how much I LOVE strengthening the gluteus medius, or "side butt" as i like to call it. 🍑 Not only does this muscle have a huge responsibility in stabilizing the hips but a weak glute med can contribute greatly to knee and ankle injuries and can make activities like running or dancing really painful.

Here's the truth, the gluteus maximus gets most of the attention. Maybe because it's shape is more visible. But if you want to develop big, round aesthetic looking glutes then you need to include some gluteus medius exercises in your routine. It's a must!

Especially, if you want to have that round curvy look around your hip area such as an hour glass figure.⏳ Complete each move for 12 reps and 3 sets each!

Home workout guides + meal plans: click the link inside my bio!

How I feel on my period versus how I feel off 😅😂

i’ve been a little down on myself lately and I love following accounts that shows these type of photos!! Gosh they are so empowering and uplifting. I’ve posted these types of things for a few years now, but now I find myself needing to see them more than ever. Please know that you are not alone! Trainers gain weight, too. But instead of rushing to try to get the weight off as fast as I possibly can (which I would never recommend for anyone), I’m choosing to embrace every step of the way. After all, I want to FEEL better. 🖤💖

On a happy note, mama is down from 151lbs to 146lbs! as I mentioned a few posts ago. My weight crept up over the last two years and would always yo-yo to the moon and back. Now that things in my life are back to normal and happier, I made some changes to get back to where I was. Nothing was wrong with 151 pounds! Not at all. However I noticed my knees hurting, getting winded during workouts easily, and my clothes just didn’t fit anymore. I made some changes and I’m happy to be on this journey. I’m not looking for a certain weight number, I just want to go by how I feel and how my clothes fit.

I think the biggest thing that I’ve noticed is when I started intermittent fasting again. I’m currently doing the 16:8. I love it because it gives your body a break to heal and digest everything. Plus I’m not a huge breakfast person anyway!

If you would like to follow along with me, click the link inside of my bio to shop workout and meal plans. I will post updates here & there on how things are going!

Do this 10 minute workout every morning to see results! See the rest of the moves + full workout video by clicking the link inside of my bio.

BACK FAT WORKOUT✨
-
Back fat can attack in a few different areas. Most men and women experience fat in one of these three areas:
Bra line fat. If you get excess fat that spills over the back of your bra strap, then you've got upper back fat.
Waistline fat. If your fat folds near the back of your waist, then you've got mid-back fat.
Muffin top fat. If like many women, you get a pocket of fat that spills over the top of your jeans in the back, then you've got lower back fat.
-
The best way to combat back fat is by limiting body fat all over while strengthening or building upon your back muscles.
-
1. DIET: calorie-controlled diet will help you to lose fat all over your body. Unfortunately, you can't decide exactly where the fat loss will occur first. But you can eat a diet that includes plenty of lean protein to promote muscle growth.
-
2. EXERCISE. High-intensity cardiovascular exercise will help you to burn fat and calories. Then, depending on where you hold the most back fat, you can tone muscles in the surrounding areas to give your back a leaner appearance by using the exercises within this video. -
Aim for 30 seconds, 4 sets for the floor moves and 15 reps, 3 sets for the weighted moves.

node.text:
May I mention just how important it is to find someone who LOVES you? No… I don’t mean loving you when it’s convenient for them or when you’re acting however they expect you to act. But those who truly love you-unconditionally? That shit is rare. I’ve waited so long to find someone who lights my fire, and, guys, I think I’ve got it. There are some amazing things that are coming along… 🤭 and I can’t wait to share it all with you. But I just want to say how thankful I am for this human being who gives himself to me and my children. I haven’t had that in a while.

So honestly thank you guys for supporting this. This is it. I’m so ready for my fairytale! He gets me like nobody ever has. I love his family and he loves mine. It almost feels too good to be true.

Third times the charm right? Counting my blessings y’all. I hope y’all do the same 💖😍

node.text:
PSA: It can be pretty easy to hide weight gain. For those who have gained weight (🙋🏽‍♀️), posing and lighting can do wonders. 

Let me preface this by saying: it’s OKAY to gain weight. It happens. We were not meant to stay at the same weight daily.

This has been the heaviest I’ve weighed in a few years-probably since taking out my implants. Two weeks ago, I sat at 151lbs and my weight was steadily going up. While my weight gain may not appear drastic, I felt it. My knees started hurting. I felt lethargic. I felt bloated. My clothes stopped fitting. My anxiety got worse. I had less stamina and when I tried to run, I was breathless. According to BMI (which is crap anyway), I was overweight. I had enough. At 63 inches, I knew this didn’t feel right.

I made some changes and got serious and now, today, I’m at 147lbs, steadily going back down. Woohoo!

When my divorce process started, I was 116lbs-a little too small IMO. After going through a two year divorce process (finally over it), a narcissistic relationship, starting a second business, and many other life changes, I put fitness (and mostly my eating!) on the back burner.

So what changes have I made?
1. Intermittent fasting- I like the 16:8.
2. Cooking more meals from home (such as the ones in the Strong Body Guide)
3. Keeping it cool on the carbohydrates. Carbs aren’t the enemy. However my body responds well to a lower-carb (not zero carb) diet.
4. More cardio! I’ve been wearing my watch more and keeping track of steps and calories burned.
5. Slowly getting back into my home workouts + CrossFit.
6. Limiting alcohol.

I don’t have an ideal number or weight on the scale in mind. I honestly don’t care to get to a certain number on the scale anyway. BUT I do know how my body feels at each number range. I plan to keep working until my clothes fit better and I feel better!

So here’s to getting back to it! I will share another update in a couple of weeks or so. In the meantime, ill keep posting my meals & workouts.

If you would like to work out with me, click the link in my bio to visit my website for homework out guides and meal plans. If you would like free workout videos, visit my YouTube as well!

node.text:
Being a soccer mom and a dance mom, I know that proper hydration is key. I am happy that there is finally a CLEAN electrolyte drink for them to use. It's called Kinderlyte from @kinderfarmsUSA.

What sets it apart? It hydrates 3x faster than water without artificial sweeteners, colors, flavors or preservatives and it has LESS sugar than other brands. They use simple ingredients, like those you’d find on a farm.

This drink is also good for  stomach viruses, traveling, heat exhaustion, and diarrhea.Also, if you are an adult-bye bye hangovers!

I always keep some in my pantry just in case we need quick, healthy hydration! Be sure to give it a try to see the difference!

You can find it at Walgreens, CVS, Rite Aid, Target and Albertsons nationwide. Check out
@kinderfarmsUSA to learn more #ChooseKinder #ad

node.text:
This has been one of my favorite snacks lately! Egg salad with a hint of dill pickle. I like to whip this up whenever I’m craving a high-protein, low carb snack to munch on throughout the day. Instead of putting on bread, I prefer the crunch of romaine!

Ingredients:
6 boiled eggs, chopped
4 tbsp pickle juice 
1 pickle, chopped 
1/4 onion chopped 
2 tbsp Mayo
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp dill weed
Salt & pepper to taste

Directions:
Mix in a bowl.
Serve however you’d like!

Stretches for tight hips + back pain 💥 Tight hip flexors can lead to a lot of issues including back and even knee pain! When you think about it, your hip flexors are near the core of your body and they control how your body moves. These stretches will help to relieve some of the pain you feel all over your body starting at the hips! Try to hold each stretch for 30 seconds or more. Stretch at least once a day.
